rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A wearable electronic device that records a person's activity relating to fitness and health, e.g. heart rate, steps walked, calories consumed, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Activity Tracker

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information on a person's use of an activity tracker device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Activity Tracker Usage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies an action that is being tracked by the activity tracker.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the activity tracker whose usage is being tracked.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Activity Tracker

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the category of the activity that is being tracked, e.g. steps walked, floors climbed, distance traversed, heart rate, water drunk, calories eaten, and calories burned.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the level of the activity that is being tracked, e.g. sleep, sedentary activity, light activity, moderate activity, and vigorous activity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Level

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies whether or not the given information is real or aspirational.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Normativity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the person using the activity tracker.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Person

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the time over which the value reported is valid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Time Valid

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the unit of measure for the value recorded by the activity tracker for the given usage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the value that is recorded by the activity tracker for a particular usage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates how the value of the property of mso:commerce.activity_tracker_usage.value was derived, e.g. whether it is the average, the maximum or the minimum over a given set of figures.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Value Qualifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An electric device that cools homes by removing heat from indoor air and venting it outside.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Air Conditioner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An electronic device that removes particles from the air.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Air Purifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Any home appliance that processes air in some way, e.g. by cooling it, heating it, humidifying it, dehumidifying it, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Air Treatment Device

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an air treatment device to the amount of air, in cubic metres per second, that the device is abled to process.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Air Flow

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an air treatment device to a textual description of the maximum size of a room where the device can be effectively used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recommended Room Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that can playback sound, either from a recording or from a broadcast received by the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Audio Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that specifies whether or not the car audio player includes an equalizer, a component that allows the user to fine-tune the frequency content of an audio signal.
The number of sources from which the audio player can receive audio data.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Audio Player Input Channels

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an audio player to the number of amplifiers included with the player. An amplifier is a device for increasing the amplitude of electrical signals in sound reproduction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Amplifiers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an audio player to the number of speakers included with the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Speakers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of channels to which the audio player can send the reproduced sound.
The type of sound reproduced by the audio player, e.g. stereo, surround sound, Hi-Fi, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sound Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Speakers that are included with the given audio player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Audio Player Speakers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The radio frequency bands that can be received by the audio player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tuner Bands

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that is capable of scanning and recording printed bar codes, e.g. the ones found on product labels.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bar Code Reader

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A stand-alone device that is used to cook food by heating it from below. Barbecue grills can be powered by gas, charcoal or electricity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Barbecue Grill

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that aggregates information about the expected life of a battery with respect to a particular use of a given device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Battery Life

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the expected time, in minutes, that batteries are expected to work for the use of the given device before they need to be recharged.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a description of a particular use of a given device, e.g. still frames or video recording.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Use

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type collecting data on the battery capacity and type used in a particular type of mso:electronics_product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Battery

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a battery relationship to the capcity of the specified mso:engineering.battery_cell_type used in instances of the device type given.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the capacity of the given battery in watt-hours. This property is needed, because in some cases the capacity of a battery is given in watt-hours or kilowatt-hours, and it is not possible to convert between these measures and amperes per hour, which is the measure used in the property mso:commerce.battery_relationship.capacity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Capacity Watt Hour

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of batteries used by the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a battery relationship to the mso:commerce.electronics_product that uses that type and capacity of battery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the size of the batteries used by the device, e.g. "AA", "C", "D", etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a battery relationship to the mso:engineering.battery_cell_type used in instances of the device type specified.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all skin and beauty products. These are those products used to beautify the skin, like mascara, eyeshadow, and blush, and maintain the skin, like moisturizers, toners, and sunscreen.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beauty Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail establishments that specialize in selling products to furnish the bedrooms and bathrooms of a home.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bed and Bath Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains models of bicycles, e.g. Raleigh Burner and Explorer 600.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bicycle

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a model of bicycle to the category of bike, e.g. mountain bike, recumbent, hybrid, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bike Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a model of bicycle to the number of speeds on the model, e.g. 10 or 12.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Speeds

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Optical devices for viewing remote objects that contain two lens, one for each eye.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Binoculars

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Information about the prism system of the binoculars. The prism system in a pair of binoculars is what allows the user to see a correctly oriented image.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Binoculars Prism System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An electronic device that is used to mix or emulsify food or other organic substances. Note that blenders are distinguished from mixers in that blenders contain a receptacle for the food.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Blender

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company, product or service that is recognizable to a signficant segment of the public. Note that some brands are local, while others are national and even international.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brand

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A software application, e.g. a smartphone or tablet app, that is associated with the given brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Application

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A color that is associated with the given brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A short, catchy phrase that is used to increase consciousness of the associated brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Slogan

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The company that owns the brand, e.g. McDonalds owns the brand Big Mac.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Company

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The relationship between a brand and a consumer product, e.g. the relationship between the brand Barbie and the consumer product Stolen Magic Barbie Doll.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Consumer Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Subbrands of the given brand, e.g. Big Mac is a subbrand of the McDonalds brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subbrands

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The industry associated with the brand. Note that this property is part of commerce.brand rather than business.operation, because a business may have brands in multiple industries, e.g. conglomerates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Industry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a brand to the date that the brand was introduced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Introduced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A graphic design associated with the brand, e.g. the double golden arches of the McDonalds brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Logo
Name or Alias

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Superbrands of the given brand, e.g. McDonalds is a superbrand of the Big Mac brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Superbrands

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The relationship between a brand and a product line, e.g. the relationship between the brand iPod and the product line iPod nano.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Line

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An attribute generated using the commerce category, freebase industry or predicted commerce category (predicted using products)
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Relevant Category or Industry
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use commerce.brand.industry instead, whose expected type is business.industry rather than string. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:commerce.brand.industry ]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A video that is associated with the brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Videos

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type to store information about the colors associated with a particular brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brand Colors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A color associated with the brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether the given color is the main color associated with the brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dominant Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date after which the given color was associated with the brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beginning Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date until which the given color was associated with the brand.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that is designed to record still or moving images.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Camera

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to the number of autofocus points that the camera has. An autofocus point in a viewfinder or camera screen indicates the part of the image where the camera is focusing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Autofocus Points

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The subclass that the camera is marketed and sold under, e.g. compact, consumer, prosumer, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Camera Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to a free-form descriptor of how the amount of light reaching the photographic film or image sensor is determined. Some examples of such descriptors are: manual, automatic, and aperture-priority.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Exposure Mode

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of film used by the camera, e.g. 35mm, APS, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Film Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a camera to the range in meters over which the flash included with the camera can be used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flash Range

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of flash included in the camera, e.g. multi-flash or high-speed flash.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flash type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to the maximum number of photos that can be taken per second.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Frames per Second

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to a measure of the maximum film speed or sensitivity of the camera as defined by the International Standards Organization (ISO).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: ISO speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A measure of the width of the opening of the camera through which light is admitted. This is the ratio of the camera's focal length to the diameter of the entrance pupil, and it is known as the f-number, f-ratio or f-stop. Note that this is the maximum aperture value, and the minimum aperture value, if there is one, should be recorded under mso:commerce.camera.lens_aperture_minimum.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lens aperture

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A measure of the width of the opening of the camera through which light is admitted. This is the ratio of the camera's focal length to the diameter of the entrance pupil, and it is known as the f-number, f-ratio or f-stop. Note that this is the minimum aperture value, and the maximum aperture value, if there is one, should be recorded under mso:commerce.camera.lens_aperture.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lens Aperture Minimum

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of interface between the body of the given camera and compatible lenses. Note that this property is only applicable to cameras that have interchangeable lenses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lens Mount

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to the maximum ISO speed (outside of the native range offered by the manufacturer) which the camera is capable of supporting.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Expandable ISO Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The longest distance at which the lens included with the camera can focus.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Focal Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The longest distance at which a 35mm camera that is equivalent to the given camera would be able to focus.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Focal Length Equivalence 35mm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a camera to the maximum length of time, in seconds, that the shutter can be open for a given exposure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Shutter Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to a description of metering used by the camera based on light striking the image sensor of the camera.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Liveview Metering

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to a description of metering used by the camera based on a built-in metering sensor of the camera.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Viewfinder Metering

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to the minimum ISO speed (outside of the native range offered by the manufacturer) which the camera is capable of supporting.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Expandable ISO Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The shortest distance at which the lens included with the camera can focus.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum focal length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The shortest distance at which a 35mm camera that is equivalent to the given camera would be able to focus.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Focal Length Equivalence 35mm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to a measure of the minimum film speed or sensitivity of the camera as defined by the International Standards Organization (ISO).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum ISO Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a camera to the minimum length of time, in seconds, that the shutter can be open for a given exposure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Shutter Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The maximum magnification of the zoom feature included with the camera.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Optical zoom range

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to a description of the standard implemented by the camera for camera-to-printer connection.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Standard

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to a descriptor for the type of shutter included in the camera.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shutter Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a camera to a viewfinder that is part of the camera.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Viewfinder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The classification of the component of the camera through which the user looks to compose and focus the photograph.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Viewfinder type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A camera accessory that is used to alter the quality of light that enters the lens of the camera.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Camera Filter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A lens or set of lenses that is used with a camera to make images of objects on photographic film or on other media.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Camera Lens

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail outlets that specialize in selling cameras and camera accessories.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Camera Shop

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Any consumer product that includes one or more lenses as essential components.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cameras and Optics Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The distance of the eye from the exterior of an eyepiece of an optical instrument at which the full viewing angle can be seen.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Eye Relief

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The diameter in meters of one of the lenses of the optical instrument.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lens Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of interface between the body of the given optics device and compatible lenses, e.g. C-mount or CS-mount. Note that this property is only applicable to devices that have interchangeable lenses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lens Mount

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an optics device to a type of lens used by the device, e.g. telephoto, wide-angle, zoom, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lens Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The ratio between the smallest and largest focal length of the lens or lenses included with the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Magnification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.camera to its ratio of the lens's focal length to the diameter of the entrance pupil.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: F-number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that can playback sound, either from a recording or from a broadcast received by the device, and that is intended to be installed in an automobile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Car Audio Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The size of the car audio player expressed in number of DINs, defined by ISO standard 7736.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Car Audio Player Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that can playback video from a DVD-formatted disc and that is intended to be installed in an automobile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Car DVD Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A component of an audio system whose function is to make a sound recording or broadcast audible and which is intended to be installed in a car.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Car Speaker

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that is capable of reading data from either a memory card or a smart card.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Card Reader

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that is capable of reading and possibly writing writing to a compact disc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: CD Drive

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property that indicates the type of technology, if any, included in the compact disc drive that allows users to etch images and text on the label side of the disc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Laser Labelling Technology

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that can transmit and receive phone calls over a radio network in a broad geographic area.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cell Phone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Total amount of time that the phone would run while in idle mode and without a recharge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Battery Standby Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Total amount of time that the phone would run while in active use and without a recharge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Battery Talk Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The still-image camera that is included with the cell phone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cell Phone Camera

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The company that provides the telecommunications service for the phone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cell Phone Carrier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the cell phone contains two SIM (Subscriber Identity Module) cards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dual Sim Cell Phone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The style of the cell phone, e.g. bar, slider, flip phone, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cell Phone Form Factor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The radio frequency spectrum used by the cell phone, e.g. GSM, CDMA, WCDMA, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cell Phone Radio Frequency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business or individual that specializes in cleaning.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cleaning Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that removes moisture from clothing by heating and circulating it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Clothes Dryer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a clothes dryer to the maximum speed of the drum of the dryer in rotations per minute (rpm).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Spin Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A handheld appliance that is heated and used to remove wrinkles from clothing and other fabrics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Clothes Iron

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An electronic device that is used to make coffee drinks. This type includes drip coffee makers, percolators, and espresso machines.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coffee Maker

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the coffee maker includes a timer that can be set by the user.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Programmable Timer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the coffee maker includes a drip tray that is separable from the main unit for emptying and/or washing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Removable Drip Tray

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A single home appliance that has the functionality of both a washing machine and a clothes dryer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Combination Washer Dryer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Establishments that specialize in maintaining and fixing computers
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Service and Repair Shop

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all consumer products. Consumer products are the tangible commodities produced and then consumed by the consumer to satisfy current wants or needs. Consumer goods are those goods consumed rather than used in the production of another good.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Consumer Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of months since the consumer product was released. Note that the age can be computed from the value of the property commerce.consumer_product_availability, but in many cases only the age of the product is known.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Age

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a consumer product to information about the age groups, e.g. infants, teens, adults, for whom the product is recommended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Age Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date that general public is informed by the company that the consumer product will be manufactured. Note that the announced date is typically far in advance of the release date of a product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Announced Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the product has to be put together by the buyer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assembly Required

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an instance of mso:commerce.consumer_product to the availability relationship(s) that represent the dates and locations of the product's availability.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Availability

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The brand associated with the consumer product. A brand is recognizable to a significant segment of the public. Note that some brands are local, while others are national and even international.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brand

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that is used to provide information to an electronics product, e.g. a QWERTY or AZERTY keyboard, a touch sensitive keyboard, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Input Device

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The operating systems that can be used with the given input device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: OS Compatibility

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A consumer product that is a leaf-level node in the product catalog of the manufacturer/distributor. In other words, in this case there are no variants of the product. This level of products is often referred to as SKUs (stock-keeping units).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Inventory Item

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an inventory item to a location where the item is available for sale.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Market

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an inventory item to the corresponding product family of the item.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Family

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all pieces of jewelry. These are decorative items worn for personal adornment and includes types like necklaces, earrings, and bracelets.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Jewelry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a piece of jewelry to a description of the device, if any, that fastens the jewelry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Clasp

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a piece of jewelry to a gemstone that is part of the jewelry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gemstone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a piece of jewelry to the proportion of precious metal in the alloy composing the jewelry, expressed as the number of karats.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Karats

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a piece of jewelry to a description of the metal and the purity of a metal that is part of the jewelry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Metal Purity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a piece of jewelry to the number of gemstones that are part of the jewelry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Stones

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a piece of jewelry to the element of the jewelry that holds a gemstone or set of gemstones, e.g. a metal ring.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Setting

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a piece of jewelry to information about the size of the jewelry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An electronic device that is used to separate juice from fresh fruits and vegetables.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Juicer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling items to furnish and/or equip the kitchen and/or dining room, e.g. dining room tables, chairs, bar stools, butchers blocks, glass tables, and bar stools.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Kitchen Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A cooking unit that consists of several burners and an oven.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Kitchen Stove

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in cleaning clothing, using dry solvents or water and detergent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Laundry and Dry Cleaning Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail establishments that specialize in selling products and services relating to the external spaces of a home and its associated property. See commerce.home_and_housewares_store for businesses that offer products and services relating to the internal spaces of a home.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lawn and Garden Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A machine that is used to trim grass, whether powered by hand, electricity or gas.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lawn Mower

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail establishment that specialize in selling electric devices to provide illumination and circulate air, e.g. light fixtures and ceiling fans.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lighting and Fans Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling cut lumber or other wood products (e.g. plywood and particle board) that are used to build and finish homes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lumber Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that is capable of reading data from a memory card. A smart card is a card containing a flash memory data storage device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory Card Reader

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An electric appliance that cooks food by means of electromagnetic radiation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Microwave Oven

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An electronic device that mixes food or other organic substances. Note that blenders are distinguished from mixers in that blenders contain a receptacle for the food.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mixer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A portable digital consumer electronics device that is capable of playing audio files and, in some cases, displaying images and playing video media.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mobile Digital Media Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling portable electronic devices used for voice or data communication over a network of specialized base stations to other mobile users.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mobile Phone Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling products that are customarily used in offices, e.g. calendars, rubber stamps, stationery and paper, pens, pencils, organizers, clipboards, binders, perforators, collators, cutters, trimmers, paper joggers, whiteboards, and projectors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Office Supply Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A barbecue grill that is designed to be used outdoors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Outdoor Barbecue Grill

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling products for furnishing the outdoor spaces of a home, e.g. birdhouses, feeders, fencing, flags and banners, garden art and ornaments, gazebos, mailboxes, pots and containers, stepping stones, sundials, water fountains, weathervanes, and wind chimes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Outdoor Furniture and Decor Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail businesses that sell garden tools and supplies, including seeds and plants.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Plant Nursery

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling fixtures that are part of a system in the home for delivering and draining away water.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Plumbing Fixtures Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail outlets that specialize in selling supplies for swimming pools, hot tubs, saunas, spas, and other similar installations. Products offered include pool lifts, electronic control systems, pool water purifier and water filter, solar heating, sanitation, pumps, and diving boards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pool and Spa Supply Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A machine that is used to make popcorn.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Popcorn Maker

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the number and kinds of ports on a particular electronic device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Port

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the kind of port that the specified number of ports have on the given device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Port Label

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of ports on the given device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Ports

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration of the kinds of ports on an electronic device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Port Label
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is no longer needed, now that the expected type of mso:commerce.port.label has been changed to string. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value indicating a high-definition multimedia port.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: HDMI

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value indicating a universal serial bus port.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: USB

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that receives text and graphic output from a computer or from a physical text and transfers the data to paper.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a printer to the maximum number of dots, characters, etc. that the printer is capable of rendering when printing in black and white.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Black and White Resolution

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a printer to the maximum number of dots, characters, etc. that the printer is capable of rendering when printing in color.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color Resolution

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The speed of the printer when the printer is making color copies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Color Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates the specific colors that are rendered by the given printer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Color Support

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates whether the printer is capable of printing on both sides of a sheet of paper.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Duplex Printer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Average number of pages per month that the printer is expected to handle with ordinary maintenance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Duty Cycle

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a printer to a type of media, e.g. transparencies or photographic paper, that the printer is capable of imprinting.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Media Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The sizes of paper that the printer accommodates. Note that in many cases the value for this property will be a standard descriptor, e.g. "Legal" or "A4".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Paper Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The sizes of paper rolls that the printer accommodates. Note that the expected type here is a string, because of the wide variety of formats in which the data is recorded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Roll Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The speed of the printer (in number of sheets per minute) when the printer is making black and white copies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of technology that is used to create the print outs, e.g. thermal, laser, dot-jet, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Technology

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates the category under which the printer is marketed and sold, e.g. personal printer, CD printer, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains electronic devices that have printing and/or scanning functionality.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Printer Scanner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a printer/scanner to the number of colors that can be rendered by the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Colors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all products. Products are those commodities that are created by a process. These products may be then sold directly to a consumer, mso:commerce.consumer_product, or used or sold for other purposes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a product to any action that can be performed on the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a product to unstructured information about how to maintain the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Care and Cleaning

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a product to the type of fuel that is used by the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuel

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: roperty relating an mso:commerce.product to its mso:commerce.product_edition_type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Label

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property linking a product to a standard descriptor of the lifecycle stage where the product is currently located, e.g. "active", "discontinued", "obsolete", etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lifecycle Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:commerce.product to its mso:business.manufacturing_relationship. This data includes the start and end dates for manufacturing this product, the manufacturer, and the number produced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manufacturing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product_model to the string that is the model's identifying number.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Model Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a product to the number of separate pieces that make up the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Pieces

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a product to the number of units of the product that were produced by a given date.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Units

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product to the date of its original manufacture.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Original Manufacture Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product to its product code. The product code is an identifier for products that are ready to be sold or marketed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Code

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product to its safety information, the warnings, contraindications, and potential side effects of the supplement.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Safety Information

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a product to information about the number of units of the product that were sold in a given time frame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sales Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a product to detailed, technical information about the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Specifications

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product to its theme as an mso:media_common.subject. The theme of a product serves to relate different products into a unit that is less formal than a product line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Theme

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a product to a range of numbers indicating the cost per unit of the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit Cost

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a product to a free-form descriptor of the type of users of the product, e.g. consumers, professionals, prosumers, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Users

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type specifying information about where and when a consumer product will be available for purchase.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Availability

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product_availability relationship to the date, if any, when the product was or will be discontinued.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product_availability relationship to the location of product availability.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product_availability relationship to the product that would be available during the specified time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product_availability relationship to the date of product availability.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Start Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration of the possible ways in which the functioning of a complex product can be manipulated, viz. mechanical, electronic, or a combination of the two.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Control Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates that the force required by the product is provided by a combination of mechanical and electronic means.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Combination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates that all of the force is provided by an electrical system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Electronic

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates that the user has to provide all of the force needed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mechanical

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data on edition types. These are the special 'collector editions' or 'limited editions' for products that may have special features or may be limited in numbers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Edition Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A product that covers a number of product variants. For example, this type contains the Cuisinart Food Processor product, because it has the following variants: the 9-cup version, the 12-cup version, and the 14-cup version. Note that this type is exclusive with mso:commerce.inventory_item.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Family

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a product family to inventory items that are part of the product family.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Inventory Item

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Something that is perceived by a user to be a problem with an electronic device or with software running on a device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Issue

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The underlying condition that gives rise to the product issue, e.g. a laptop will not power up because its battery does not have a charge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cause

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a product issue to the product or products that have the issue.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Consumer Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A procedure which is intended to settle the product issue, e.g. solving connectivity issues with a mobile device by setting airplane mode to "off".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Resolution

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a product issue to an indication or sign of the issue, e.g. not being able to connect a laptop to a wireless network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Symptom

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all recalls. These are the requests by a manufacturer to return a defective product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Recall

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product_recall to the company responsible for the recall.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Company

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product_recall to the product recalled.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.product_recall to the text description of the reason for the recall.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reason

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type for collecting information about the number of units of a given product sold in a given time frame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Sales

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The beginning of the time frame for which the sales information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Begin Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The end of the time frame for which the sales information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of units of the given product that were sold in the given time frame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Items

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The location, if any, to which the sales information is restricted. For example, one might want to break out sales information for the United States, Canada, Japan, France, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Market

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An appliance that contains a mechanical fan and often a light that is designed to be installed above a kitchen stove and to provide ventilation and light.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Range Hood

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A home appliance that is used to cool foods and thus reduce spoilage. Generally, a refrigerator consists of two compartments: one that is cooled to a temperature just above freezing and one that is cooled to a temperature below freezing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Refrigerator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a refrigerator to a standard descriptor for the type of ice cube trays included with the appliance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ice Cube Tray Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects data on a retailer selling a product for a particular price in a given market for a certain period of time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Retailer Price

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a country where the product is offered by the retailer at the given price.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the discount, if any, of the offer as a percentage with respect to the regular price for the product in the offer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discount

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the conditions, if any, under which the retailer will provide free shipping of the product offered.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Free Shipping

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a descriptor for the availability of the given product in the given offer, e.g. in-stock, out-of-stock, pre-order, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Item Availability

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an offer to a textual description of events for which the offer is intended, e.g. Christmas, birthdays, parties, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Occasion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that specifies whether or not the offer applies to both retail outlets and online orders or just to online orders.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Online Only

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the original packaging in which the offer is contained. Note that this may be different from the packaging that is used to ship the offer, which is indicated with the following path: mso:commerce.retailer_price_relationship.shipping -> mso:commerce.retailer_product_shipping.package_type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Packaging

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.retailer_price_relationship to the dated money value that is the price the retailer charges for the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Price

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.retailer_price_relationship to the mso:commerce.consumer_product
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the condition of the product that is offered by the given retailer, e.g. new or used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Condition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of product units in the given offer if the number is greater than 1.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Quantity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the size of the product in the given offer, e.g. small, medium or large.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.retailer_price_relationship to the retailer selling the product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Retailer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies information about sales tax for the given product offer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sales Tax

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a product offer by a retailer to shipping information that applies to the offer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shipping

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the time interval, if any, during which the offer is available.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Time Valid

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property indicating that the offer has been confirmed to be a real offer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Verified

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects shipping information.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Retailer Product Shipping

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies, in a generic way, the time when the package will be delivered, e.g. by 4:30 PM the next day.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Delivery Commitment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the location to which the given item will be shipped.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the location from which the given item will be shipped.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Origin

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the category of the package, e.g. medium box, extra large box, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Package Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the price for shipping the item.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Price

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the company responsible for shipping the item.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shipper

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the weight of the product in the offer when it is shipped.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the sales tax, if any, that is assessed on a purchase.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sales Tax

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total amount of sales tax for a given purchase.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Amount

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the location where the given sales tax applies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that is capable of converting a page of text and/or graphic content into a digital file.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Scanner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates that the scanner is capable of converting both sides of a page into a digital file without any manipulation of the page by the user.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Duplex Scanner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration type for sectors. This includes enumerations like industrial, residential, and commercial.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sector Enumeration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the commercial sector.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commercial

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the industrial sector.
Enumeration representing the mobile sector.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mobile

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration representing the residential sector.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Residential

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A camera that is specifically designed to be used for security purposes, e.g. a closed-circuit camera installed at an ATM or a convenience store.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Security Camera

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of security systems. These systems are the electronics placed in private residences and in businesses that are designed to detect unauthorized entry into the home or business. Mostly the purposes is to protect against theft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Security System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.security_system to the automatic external light pass control option.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Auto Iris Control

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A machine that is used to stitch fabric.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sewing Machine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that is capable of reading data from a smart card. A smart card is a card containing an embedded microchip which can store application-specific data, e.g. for electronic payments or identify verification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Smart Card Reader

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The specific type of smart card reader, e.g. magnetic card reader, RF proximity reader, MICR reader, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Smart Card Reader Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An wireless, interactive device that can respond to voice commands and perform intelligent functions, e.g. Amazon Echo and Google Home.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Smart Speaker

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A component of an audio system whose function is to make a sound recording or broadcast audible.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Speaker

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A speaker crossover splits the audio input signal into a number of channels that can then be reproduced by different speakers or speaker components. This property records the number of channels associated with the speaker crossover.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Crossover Channel Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The measure of the speaker from side to side and through the center.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Speaker Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The maximum amount of audio power, expressed in watts, that the speaker is capable of generating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Speaker Maximum Output Power

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The maximum amount of audio power, expressed in watts, that the speaker is designed to output over a sustained period of time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Speaker Nominal Output Power

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Information about the type or class of speakers, e.g. active, passive, coaxial, triaxial, dual core, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Speaker Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that resembles a bicycle but is used for exercise rather than transportation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stationary Bicycle

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all telephones. These are the telecommunication devices that allow for communication over long distances by converting sound into electronic signals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Telephone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the telephone has caller ID, i.e. a service that automatically transmits the caller's telephone number to the telephone called.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Caller ID

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of parties that can participate in a conference call that is initiated by the given telephone.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Conference Calling

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the given telephone is capable of initiating and receiving conference calls.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Conference Support

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the telephone has a handset locator, i.e. a service that automatically rings the handset when it cannot be located.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Handset Locator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all television sets. These are the electronic devices that combine a tuner, screen, and speakers to view television.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Television

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of technology used in the television set, e.g. LCD, LED, rear projection, 3D, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Television Set Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration type containing values for the three possible settings of a thermostat: off, cooling, and heating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Thermostat Mode

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A value indicating that only air conditioning should be used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cooling

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A value indicating that only heating should be used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heating

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A value that indicates that the thermostat function has been turned off, i.e. no heating/cooling is desired.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Off

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A digital camera that is capable of taking photographs that have an apparent dimension of depth, as well as width and height.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: 3D Digital Camera

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A digital video recorder that is capable of taking videos that have an apparent dimension of depth, as well as width and height.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: 3D Digital Video Recorder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Webcams whose captured images have an apparent dimension of depth, as well as width and height.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: 3D Webcam

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A small, electric appliance that is designed to toast bread products. Note that this type covers both pop-up toasters and toaster ovens.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Toaster

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An exercise device that allows the user to walk or run while staying in the same place.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Treadmill

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Devices that are capable of both receiving and transmitting radio signals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Two-way Radio

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The radio frequency bands that the device is capable of receiving and transmitting, e.g. AM, FM, VHF, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Radio Channels

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates whether or not the given radio has a function to notify the user of an incoming transmission by vibrating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Vibrating Alert

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates whether or not the given radio's transmission function can be activated simply by talking.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Voice-Activated

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A digital camera that is capable of taking photographs underwater.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Underwater Digital Camera

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A digital video recorder that is capable of taking videos under water.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Underwater Digital Video Camera

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An electric device that cleans flooring by means of an air pump that sucks up dirt and dust.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Vacuum Cleaner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An optics device that shows the field of view and is used for siting another device, e.g. a camera or firearm.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Viewfinder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a viewfinder to the amount of the field of view of the camera, expressed as a percentage, that is covered by the viewfinder.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coverage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a viewfinder to a number expressing the ratio of the size of image in the viewfinder to the size of the image in the camera itself.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Effective Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that is capable of recording sound, especially the human voice, so that it can be archived and played back.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Voice Recorder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that removes dirt and stains from laundry by circulating it in a mixture of water and detergent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Washing Machine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a washing machine to the maximum speed of the drum of the washing machine in rotations per minute (rpm).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Spin Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all watches. These are the time pieces worn on a wrist, sometimes used as an adornment. Smartwatches are those watches that incorporate an increasing number of functions, along the lines of PDAs or smartphones.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Watches

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.watch_model to the mso:engineering.material that makes up the band.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Band Material

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:commerce.watch_model to the mso:engineering.material that makes up the case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Case Material

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An appliance that is used to heat water for the taps in a home.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Water Heater

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Video cameras that are capable of broadcasting motion images over the internet in real time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Webcam

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in cleaning windows.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Window Cleaning
